that I am loner and I get home restless and depressed.
I try to stay as much calm as possible when I'm with other people, given that I am not at the best of my moods most times. (I have a neurological condition that makes me act mad at times.)

Although I know that that I am not causing any discomfort or annoyance to anybody, I try to be tolerant and compassionate enough to keep shit to myself when I am around other people.  

During party and other gatherings that I somehow ended up. I try to be as accommodating as possible to make everybody at easy. 

It has been 2 days since that party, I feel empty and I am depressed. 

-------------

What I am looking for in this post is to understand **why I feel depressed and alone.** 

*Personal:-* I am not religious (not depressed at all), I have girl problems (didn't improve), I sleep all night and during the day (depression and anxiety disorder). 
*Practical:-* no job, live with parents (shared bedroom), no motivation to put in work academically (past outrageous work efforts, why bother?), I have no friends.

I can't blame my depression on anything, but I know that something is really wrong with having such a problem and doing nothing to improve it. 

I am not looking for a  professional or costly help. I am just on here to write it out so that I can face rationality to eventually
